18-09-30, 18:19:26","excerpt":"<p>So much has happened this week in web! Here is a great overview on UX animation, Lyft has created a colour palette tool. A brilliant article on why select boxes might not be the best option for users, and what to do with user mistake? All this and more on this weeks website design rundown. [&hellip;]</p>\n","featured_media":{"localFile":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.829268292682927,"src":"/static/dae884bde314d3100863b5647aac414c/db7af/Proper-UX-Animation-1.jpg","srcSet":"/static/dae884bde314d3100863b5647aac414c/8f9a6/Proper-UX-Animation-1.jpg 250w,\n/static/dae884bde314d3100863b5647aac414c/6a7a1/Proper-UX-Animation-1.jpg 500w,\n/static/dae884bde314d3100863b5647aac414c/db7af/Proper-UX-Animation-1.jpg 750w","sizes":"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px"}}},"title":"Proper UX Animation","alt_text":"Proper UX Animation Banner"},"categories":[{"name":"Coding"},{"name":"Design"},{"name":"General Coding"},{"name":"Inspiration"},{"name":"Ramblings"},{"name":"ReactJS"},{"name":"UX"}],"tags":[{"name":"Accessibility"},{"name":"Animated"},{"name":"Animation"},{"name":"CMS"},{"name":"CSS"},{"name":"Design"},{"name":"Framework"},{"name":"Inspiration"},{"name":"Mistakes"},{"name":"React"},{"name":"Sprint"},{"name":"Trends"},{"name":"UI"},{"name":"UX"}]}},{"node":{"id":"8b32ab30-10e4-5933-aa11-816f6944dff7","slug":"to-sticky-or-not-to-sticky","template":"","format":"standard","title":"To Sticky or Not to Sticky","date":"2018-09-18, 09:59:29","modified":"2018-09-23, 06:22:39","excerpt":"<p>Fixed headers are used across the web, with little to no thought to the user&#8217;s experience. I have just started working on a new project and am intrigued in how useful fixed headers actually are for the user. Do they help navigate the site faster or do they just get in the way? &nbsp; Very [&hellip;]</p>\n","featured_media":{"localFile":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1